==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Faucal
<hw>Fau"cal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>fauces</ets>
throat.]</ety> <def>Pertaining to the fauces, or opening of the throat;
faucial;</def> <specif>esp.,</specif> <fld>(Phon.)</fld> <def>produced
in the fauces, as certain deep guttural sounds found in the Semitic and
some other languages.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Ayin is the most difficult of the <qex>faucals</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>I. Taylor (The Alphabet).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fauces</ent>⟦br⟧
